 run from virtually everyone in some desire to be at peace.  But what was peace?  Was it found in Solitude as I had tried so hard to do?  No.  All I didst find was lonliness.  <br>
 <br>
  ...and then She had entered my life.  The circumstances were bizarre.  The situation was chance.<br>
 And in that chance, redemption.<br>
 <br>
  ..I had found a home.  She had taken me in, it seems, and showed me her world, her friends, her power.  And i was amazed.  Friends.  A word I had been unfamiliar with since i didst enter this land.  She was helping one now.  But I knew she would be here soon.<br>
 <br>
  As I lay there, the thoughts came to me, as they always did...the Ghost which I ran from...Hid from...haunted me.....but suddenly, a new thought...A woman, born of woodland magic, immense power, was there beside me....And the Ghost faded... <br>
 <br>
  Dear Tunare, is that a smile upon my lips?  A smile?<br>
 I had thought those dead and gone, fragments from a childhood I tried to forget, before being beaten down by The Man who wouldst become The Ghost......it feels good to smile...and i drift blissfully into sleep....<br>
 <br>
  ....the door opens, and i know it is her.  She hath come home.  Strewing her equipment around-ill pick it all up later...silently she slips into bed....OH MY GOD her feet are cold...but i do not move...i wrap her feet with my legs, hoping to warm them soon before i need to place an endure cold enchantment upon myself...<br>
 <br>
  ...i lean closer to her, and place a small kiss upon her cheek...and with another genuine smile, I whisper softly....<br>
 <br>
  ....&quot;Welcome Home&quot;.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=selicatiren@voiceofthedragon>Selicatiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Asp</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(2/12/03 7:18:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On I journey</span><hr size=1> Those hideous giants... How can I continue to hunt them? Each day, after I hunt I have the odd wish that I were blind so that I would never see a giant again.<br>
Tonight as I think of going to sleep, I toy with the crystal at my neck. Every time I look at it, it brings me comfort.<br>
Removing the makeshifk necklace that I have tried to fassion it and the string with it into, I gaze into it's depths, wondering what I will see tonight.<br>
<br>
I'm 9 again. I have just decided that I will dedicate my life to Fadark's champions. My parents are proud, one of the few times that they could both share a thought. They have arranged a celibration for me that night. Just close friends. Also the day I became one of the dragons. My brother, Toter, showed a rare moment of kindness and gave me the other necklace I wear.<br>
Then it is night. I relate the events of the day to my closest companion of the time, Amber.<br>
<br>
I wipe tears of joy from my eyes as the memory ends. How could I have forgotten the small kindnesses of that day? I shift the crystal to view another memory.<br>
<br>
This one is not my own. I know not whose it is. I see a small and unsure wood elf ranger... me, asking many questions. I see that young ranger from an appreciating perspective. Then I see the ranger start to talk to a stuffed cat about the harsh realities of her life. All around, there are the burnt remains of a house. I see a determination to right the wrong in the young me's eyes. I remember that night from my perspective then though.<br>
<br>
I talked to Amber because she and I were the only ones still there. I poured out my heart to that cat. Then I dried the tears from sorrow about my family and vowed to live with the burden that I must bear alone. I chose to never burden another with it. I knew that no one else need ever know about what had happened.<br>
<br>
Yet now I find that I was being watched in my time of mourning and when I decided to take my burden alone. Is this some trick imbeded into the crystal? What was that? I know not of who or what would spend that kind of time listening to a child talk to a stuffed cat. I look around to see if I am still being watched, then realize that it is useless. maybe that was just my immagineing, I've been up far too long already anyway. So I shall sleep, and then I suppose I'll slay a few more giants... oh goody.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF33>- </font><a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon>Voice of the Dragon</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1>In a Low Voice </a> <font color=#FFFF33> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
